<p> </p>
<p><strong>Worksheets, summaries, and presentations are graded on a five-point scale (0-5), five being the highest. The rubric below is used.</strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>5: perfect, grammar and content are 100% accurate and appropriate</p>
<p>4: very good, small errors in content or grammar or language. Language may not be level appropriate</p>
<p>3: good: the meaning is clear, but there are many errors in grammar and language is often inappropriate</p>
<p>2: needs work, errors in format, content, grammar are common and language often requires interpretation. Work may also be incomplete</p>
<p>1: difficult to understand or incomplete</p>
<p>0: incomplete or incomprehensible</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の基準</div><div style="margin:10px">秀　 達成目標を超えた成果を上げている　100点～90点<br>優　 達成目標に十分達している　　　　　89点～80点<br>良　 達成目標に達している　　　　　　　79点～70点<br>可　 達成目標に概ね達している　　　　　69点～60点<br>不可 達成目標に達していない　　　　　　59点以下<br><p>◎</p>
